class.description: Inorganic oxoanionic compounds in which the heaviest atom not in an oxoanion is a transition metal.

description: This compound belongs to the class of inorganic compounds known as transition metal iodates. These are inorganic compounds in which the largest oxoanion is iodate, and in which the heaviest atom not in an oxoanion is a transition metal.

direct_parent.description: Inorganic compounds in which the largest oxoanion is iodate, and in which the heaviest atom not in an oxoanion is a transition metal.
direct_parent.name: Transition metal iodates

kingdom.description: Compounds that do not contain a C atom. Exceptions are made for isocyanide/cyanide and their non-hydrocarbyl derivatives, thiophosgene, carbon diselenide, carbon monosulfide, carbon disulfide, carbon subsulfide, carbon monoxide, carbon trioxide, carbon suboxide, and dicarbon monoxide.
kingdom.name: Inorganic compounds

subclass.description: Inorganic compounds in which the largest oxoanion is iodate, and in which the heaviest atom not in an oxoanion is a transition metal.
subclass.name: Transition metal iodates

superclass.description: Compounds that contains both metal and non metal atoms.
superclass.name: Mixed metal/non-metal compounds
